    "---\n",
    "## Step 3: Within-Family Analysis (Fixed Norm = BatchNorm)\n",
    "\n",
    "Since all 10 configs use BatchNorm, let's examine the family-specific relationship.\n",
    "Within the BatchNorm family, does J_topo independently predict loss when width varies?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Within BatchNorm family: J_topo residualized by width vs loss\n",
    "# Already computed above: r_JL_W = partial correlation\n",
